    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Get blogging with Octopress.  It has a number of advantages:</p>

<ul>
<li>Jekyll based and Git-system back</li>
<li>posts and pages can be written in Markdown</li>
<li>quick and easy to deploy (Rails)</li>
<li>stlyish code snippet mark up</li>
<li>supports many plugins driven my Jekyll liquid templating</li>
</ul>


<h2>Setup Guides</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.jackiejohnston.us/blog/setting-up-an-octopress-blog-on-heroku/" title="jackiejohnston">http://www.jackiejohnston.us/blog/setting-up-an-octopress-blog-on-heroku/</a></li>
<li><a href="http://octopress.org/docs/setup/">http://octopress.org/docs/setup/</a></li>
</ul>


<h2>Octopress Command Reference</h2>

<h3>Creating a Post</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ rake new_post["Setting up a Blog"]  
</span><span class='line'># Creates source/_posts/2014-09-02-setting-up-a-blog.markdown</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Creating a Page</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ rake new_page[awesome-page]
</span><span class='line'># creates /source/awesome-page/index.markdown
</span><span class='line'> 
</span><span class='line'>$ rake new_page[awesome-page/page.html]
</span><span class='line'># creates /source/awesome-page/page.html</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Converting Markdown to HTML</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ rake generate  </span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Preview</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ rake preview  </span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Deploy on Heroku and view</h3>

<p>Create a git remote name &ldquo;heroku&rdquo; to point to you git respository on Heroku:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ git config branch.master.remote heroku  </span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Commit and deploy onto Heroku:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ git add .
</span><span class='line'>$ git commit -m "some update"
</span><span class='line'>$ git push heroku master    
</span><span class='line'>$ heroku open  </span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h2>Markdown</h2>

<p>The source posts files genereated are in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown/" title="Markdown">Markdown</a> format by default.</p>

<p>In terms of styling, take a look at <a href="http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/basics">Markdown reference</a>.  Also Octopress comes bundled with it&rsquo;s own code snippets mark up.  Check it out <a href="http://octopress.org/docs/blogging/code/">here</a>.</p>
